CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 24, 1946 reads: "Vacationing - Mrs. James Jelks and daughter, Brenda Maureen, of Gadsden, Ala., were entertained recently at the home of Mr. and Mrs. Gilbert Body of Mulford Street. The visitors have been the house guests of Mrs. Gussie Jelks, mother-in-law of the visitor. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. James Jelks wearing light colored dress, standing with daughter Brenda Maureen Jelks, on sidewalk with plants, trellis, and house in background
